UNIXPermissions.name: UNIXPermissions
UNIXPermissions.description: This textual convention defines a format to display file and directory permissions in UNIX

ClusterIdType.name: ClusterIdType
ClusterIdType.description: This textual convention defines string for a cluster-id. Get this string from node. Size defined in ClusterIdType in xmlApiObjects.xml

CertificateType.name: CertificateType
CertificateType.description: RSA Certifcate. Max possible size for the whole certificate is 4096 bytes. This type represents a segment of the certificate.

NASContainerNameType.name: NASContainerNameType
NASContainerNameType.description: Name used to identify NAS Container. Contains only letters, digits and underscores. Must begin with either letter or an underscore.

eqlNASApplianceTable.name: eqlNASApplianceTable
eqlNASApplianceTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Appliance Table. This table contains a list of NAS pools that this group is managing. TimeoutAll:60

eqlNASApplianceEntry.name: eqlNASApplianceEntry
eqlNASApplianceEntry.description: An entry (row) containing NAS Container info.

eqlNASApplianceRowStatus.name: eqlNASApplianceRowStatus
eqlNASApplianceRowStatus.description: This field is used indicate the status of this entry.

eqlNASAppliancePoolSize.name: eqlNASAppliancePoolSize
eqlNASAppliancePoolSize.description: This field is used indicate the size of the NAS Container in MB.

eqlNASApplianceEQLPoolIndex.name: eqlNASApplianceEQLPoolIndex
eqlNASApplianceEQLPoolIndex.description: This field is used to indicate the EQL pool used by the NAS appliance.

eqlNASApplianceReplRemoteUserName.name: eqlNASApplianceReplRemoteUserName
eqlNASApplianceReplRemoteUserName.description: This field is used to indicate the Username EQL will use for NAS replication for all partners.

eqlNASApplianceNFSv4Mode.name: eqlNASApplianceNFSv4Mode
eqlNASApplianceNFSv4Mode.description: This field enables or disables NFSv4 Access NAS appliance.

eqlNASContainerTable.name: eqlNASContainerTable
eqlNASContainerTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Appliance Table. This table contains a list of NAS Appliance configurations for containers the group is managing. TimeoutAll:60

eqlNASContainerEntry.name: eqlNASContainerEntry
eqlNASContainerEntry.description: An entry (row) containing NAS Container info.

eqlNASContainerIndex.name: eqlNASContainerIndex
eqlNASContainerIndex.description: Unique Identifier used to create and manage NAS Containers. When creating NAS Containers, value must be retrieved using eqlApplianceUniqueIDValue with eqlApplianceUniqueIDType set to fsid.

eqlNASContainerRowStatus.name: eqlNASContainerRowStatus
eqlNASContainerRowStatus.description: Row status variable used to manage this row.

eqlNASContainerName.name: eqlNASContainerName
eqlNASContainerName.description: Name used to identify NAS Container. Contains only letters, digits and underscores. Must begin with either letter or an underscore.

eqlNASContainerCapacity.name: eqlNASContainerCapacity
eqlNASContainerCapacity.description: Size of NAS Container in MB.

eqlNASContainerUsedSpaceAlert.name: eqlNASContainerUsedSpaceAlert
eqlNASContainerUsedSpaceAlert.description: Alert user when NAS container used space reaches certain % value of NAS container size.Default value is choosen from eqlNASApplianceConfigUsedSpaceAlert

eqlNASContainerSnapshotHardQuota.name: eqlNASContainerSnapshotHardQuota
eqlNASContainerSnapshotHardQuota.description: This threshold, represented as a % of NAS container size, triggers auto-deletion of snapshots. The oldest snapshots are deleted first. Default value is choosen from eqlNASApplianceConfigSnapHardQuota

eqlNASContainerSnapshotUsedSpaceAlert.name: eqlNASContainerSnapshotUsedSpaceAlert
eqlNASContainerSnapshotUsedSpaceAlert.description: Alert user when NAS container snapshot used space reaches certain % value of NAS container snapshot size.Default value is choosen from eqlNASApplianceConfigSnapSpaceAlert

eqlNASContainerUnixFilePermissions.name: eqlNASContainerUnixFilePermissions
eqlNASContainerUnixFilePermissions.description: This field is applicable only when Security style is set to NFS

eqlNASContainerUnixDirPermissions.name: eqlNASContainerUnixDirPermissions
eqlNASContainerUnixDirPermissions.description: This field is applicable only when Security style is set to NFS

eqlNASContainerDedupMethodType.name: eqlNASContainerDedupMethodType
eqlNASContainerDedupMethodType.description: Dedup method to use on this file system when optimization is enabled. Reserved for future use. Currently not supported.

eqlNASContainerCompressionEnabled.name: eqlNASContainerCompressionEnabled
eqlNASContainerCompressionEnabled.description: enable or disable compression. Restricted by the type of license

eqlNASContainerModificationTimeFilter.name: eqlNASContainerModificationTimeFilter
eqlNASContainerModificationTimeFilter.description: Exclude files modified less than the specified number of days before. 30 to 365 days

eqlNASContainerAccessTimeFilter.name: eqlNASContainerAccessTimeFilter
eqlNASContainerAccessTimeFilter.description: Exclude files accessed less than the specified number of days before. 30 to 365 days

eqlNASContainerExcludeFilesByNamePattern.name: eqlNASContainerExcludeFilesByNamePattern
eqlNASContainerExcludeFilesByNamePattern.description: Regular expression identifying the file name pattern to exclude from optimization. Empty string means no exclusion.

eqlNASContainerAction.name: eqlNASContainerAction
eqlNASContainerAction.description: Use this column to perform actions on this container.

eqlNASContainerDefaultUserQuota.name: eqlNASContainerDefaultUserQuota
eqlNASContainerDefaultUserQuota.description: Default quota per user when quotas are enabled on NAS Containers.

eqlNASContainerDefaultUserQuotaAlert.name: eqlNASContainerDefaultUserQuotaAlert
eqlNASContainerDefaultUserQuotaAlert.description: Specified as a percentage of default group quota as a default for containers in this nas-group. This is the amount of used space that triggers user alerts

eqlNASContainerDefaultGroupQuota.name: eqlNASContainerDefaultGroupQuota
eqlNASContainerDefaultGroupQuota.description: Default quota per group when quotas are enabled on NAS Containers.

eqlNASContainerDefaultGroupQuotaAlert.name: eqlNASContainerDefaultGroupQuotaAlert
eqlNASContainerDefaultGroupQuotaAlert.description: Specified as a percentage of default group quota as a default for containers in this nas-group. This is the amount of used space that triggers user alerts

eqlNASContainerOptimizationFilterMode.name: eqlNASContainerOptimizationFilterMode
eqlNASContainerOptimizationFilterMode.description: Specifies the filter mode to be applied to qualify files for data reduction. user-filters implies files need to meet the access time and modify time filter criteria before they can be considered for data reduction. ignore-filters implies files are considered for data reduction irrespective of the access time and modify time filter criteria, using an access time and modification time value of 1 day. This mode is recommended for containers with archive data only.

eqlNASContainerRehydrateOnReadEnabled.name: eqlNASContainerRehydrateOnReadEnabled
eqlNASContainerRehydrateOnReadEnabled.description: Enable or disable rehydrate on read in a data reduction disabled nas container

eqlNASContainerUniqueIDTable.name: eqlNASContainerUniqueIDTable
eqlNASContainerUniqueIDTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Unique ID table. This table is used to retrieve Unique ID values when creating new objects. TimeoutAll:60

eqlNASContainerUniqueIDEntry.name: eqlNASContainerUniqueIDEntry
eqlNASContainerUniqueIDEntry.description: An entry (row) containing unique ID information.

eqlNASContainerUniqueIDType.name: eqlNASContainerUniqueIDType
eqlNASContainerUniqueIDType.description: Indicates the type of the id. For now only Snapshot and quota Ids are needed for at the container scope

eqlNASContainerUniqueIDValueLen.name: eqlNASContainerUniqueIDValueLen
eqlNASContainerUniqueIDValueLen.description: Length of the value represented by column eqlNASContainerUniqueIDValue

eqlNASContainerUniqueIDValue.name: eqlNASContainerUniqueIDValue
eqlNASContainerUniqueIDValue.description: Value of eqlNASContainerUniqueIDType represented in network byte order.

eqlNASApplianceDefaultCfgTable.name: eqlNASApplianceDefaultCfgTable
eqlNASApplianceDefaultCfgTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic (semi) Appliance Table. This table contains a list of NAS Appliance default configurations for containers the group is managing. TimeoutAll:60

eqlNASApplianceDefaultCfgEntry.name: eqlNASApplianceDefaultCfgEntry
eqlNASApplianceDefaultCfgEntry.description: An entry (row) containing NAS Container Status info.

eqlNASApplianceConfigUsedSpaceAlert.name: eqlNASApplianceConfigUsedSpaceAlert
eqlNASApplianceConfigUsedSpaceAlert.description: Specified as a percentage of NAS container size as a default for containers in this nas-group. This is the amount of used space that triggers user alerts

eqlNASApplianceConfigSnapSpaceAlert.name: eqlNASApplianceConfigSnapSpaceAlert
eqlNASApplianceConfigSnapSpaceAlert.description: Specified as a percentage of NAS container size as a default for containers in this nas-group. The is the amount of space consumed by snapshots at which user alerts are triggered

eqlNASApplianceConfigSnapHardQuota.name: eqlNASApplianceConfigSnapHardQuota
eqlNASApplianceConfigSnapHardQuota.description: Specified as a percentage of NAS container size as a default for containers in this nas-group. This is the threshold that triggers auto-deletion of snapshots. Oldest first.

eqlNASApplianceContainerUnixFilePerms.name: eqlNASApplianceContainerUnixFilePerms
eqlNASApplianceContainerUnixFilePerms.description: Define the default UNIX permissions of new files created from Windows clients. Default value is 0744

eqlNASApplianceContainerUnixDirPerms.name: eqlNASApplianceContainerUnixDirPerms
eqlNASApplianceContainerUnixDirPerms.description: Define the default UNIX permissions of new directories created from Windows clients. Default value is 0755

eqlNASApplianceContainerFileSecurity.name: eqlNASApplianceContainerFileSecurity
eqlNASApplianceContainerFileSecurity.description: Used to define how the system will maintain and verify file access security.

eqlNASApplianceDefaultUserQuota.name: eqlNASApplianceDefaultUserQuota
eqlNASApplianceDefaultUserQuota.description: Default quota per user when quotas are enabled on NAS Containers.

eqlNASApplianceDefaultUserQuotaAlert.name: eqlNASApplianceDefaultUserQuotaAlert
eqlNASApplianceDefaultUserQuotaAlert.description: Specified as a percentage of default group quota as a default for containers in this nas-group. This is the amount of used space that triggers user alerts

eqlNASApplianceDefaultGroupQuota.name: eqlNASApplianceDefaultGroupQuota
eqlNASApplianceDefaultGroupQuota.description: Default quota per group when quotas are enabled on NAS Containers.

eqlNASApplianceDefaultGroupQuotaAlert.name: eqlNASApplianceDefaultGroupQuotaAlert
eqlNASApplianceDefaultGroupQuotaAlert.description: Specified as a percentage of default group quota as a default for containers in this nas-group. This is the amount of used space that triggers user alerts

eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAllowGuestAcce.name: eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAllowGuestAccess
eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAllowGuestAcce.description: Choose whether to allow unknown users to access the share as guests.

eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSLockEnforcemen.name: eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSLockEnforcement
eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSLockEnforcemen.description: Define the types of locks that the system will enforce, in addition to share locks which are always enforced. Byte range locks allow applications to ensure data integrity. Opportunistic locks (oplocks) increase the efficiency of client machine caching and improve performance. NOTE: This software release does not support changing the locking enforcement policy. Only the default option (all-locks) is supported.

eqlNASApplianceNFSExportReadWrite.name: eqlNASApplianceNFSExportReadWrite
eqlNASApplianceNFSExportReadWrite.description: Define the access rights for the NFS export. If the access rights for the NFS export are stricter than those defined for a specific file, the file's access rights will be overridden by those of the NFS export.

eqlNASApplianceNFSExportTrustedUsers.name: eqlNASApplianceNFSExportTrustedUsers
eqlNASApplianceNFSExportTrustedUsers.description: Define which users are trusted. Other users will be identified as guests.

eqlNASApplianceOptimizationEnabled.name: eqlNASApplianceOptimizationEnabled
eqlNASApplianceOptimizationEnabled.description: Enable or disable optimization. Reserved for future use. Not supported currently.

eqlNASApplianceDedupMethodType.name: eqlNASApplianceDedupMethodType
eqlNASApplianceDedupMethodType.description: Dedup method to use on this file system when optimization is enabled. Reserved for future use. Currently not supported.

eqlNASApplianceCompressionEnabled.name: eqlNASApplianceCompressionEnabled
eqlNASApplianceCompressionEnabled.description: enable or disable compression. Restricted by the type of license. Reserved for future use. Not supported currently.

eqlNASApplianceModificationTimeFilter.name: eqlNASApplianceModificationTimeFilter
eqlNASApplianceModificationTimeFilter.description: Exclude files modified less than the specified number of days before. 30 to 365 days.

eqlNASApplianceAccessTimeFilter.name: eqlNASApplianceAccessTimeFilter
eqlNASApplianceAccessTimeFilter.description: Exclude files accessed less than the specified number of days before. 30 to 365 days.

eqlNASApplianceExcludeFilesByNamePattern.name: eqlNASApplianceExcludeFilesByNamePattern
eqlNASApplianceExcludeFilesByNamePattern.description: Regular expression identifying the file name pattern to exclude from optimization. Empty string means no exclusion.

eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusEnabl.name: eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusEnabled
eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusEnabl.description: Default which determines whether the antivirus service is disabled or enabled for a CIFS share at the time of creation.

eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusPolic.name: eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusPolicy
eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusPolic.description: Default which determines the action to be taken on a virus-infected file. This field is deprecated and unsupported. The value now always will be quarantine(0).

eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusExten.name: eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusExtensions
eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusExten.description: Default which determines which files should be / should not be scanned for viruses. This is a comma-separated list. The value of the next field determines if the files with the corresponding extensions will be scanned or not for viruses. Cannot contain wild characters * and ?. Extensions are case-insensitive.

eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusExten.name: eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusExtensionsPolicy
eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusExten.description: Default which determines whether the files whose extensions match with those specified in the field above should be scanned OR should not be scanned for viruses. This field is deprecated and unsupported. The value now always will be exclude(0).

eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusExclu.name: eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusExcludeDirPaths
eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusExclu.description: Default which determines the list of the directory paths which should not be scanned for viruses. It is a comma-separated list. Paths can contain wildcards * and ?. NOTE: * will not match several path components.

eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusLarge.name: eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusLargeFileSize
eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusLarge.description: Default which determines the largest file size in MB which is sent to Antivirus server for scanning on the fly. The files larger than the specified size are not scanned. Access to these large files will be allowed or denied based on the CIFS Antivirus Large File Open option.

eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusLarge.name: eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusLargeFileOpen
eqlNASApplianceDefaultCIFSAntivirusLarge.description: Default which determines if CIFS clients are allowed to open files larger than the value defined by AntivirusLargeFileSize.

eqlNASApplianceDefaultNFSExportsFileId32.name: eqlNASApplianceDefaultNFSExportsFileId32bit
eqlNASApplianceDefaultNFSExportsFileId32.description: Default option to trigger 32-bit compatibility mode for NFS export. When enabled, reported FileId (inode) information contains only lower 32-bits set. When disabled, reported FileId (inode) information contains full 64-bit values.

eqlNASContainerStatusTable.name: eqlNASContainerStatusTable
eqlNASContainerStatusTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic NAS Container Table. This table contains a list of NAS Appliance configurations for containers the group is managing. TimeoutAll:60

eqlNASContainerStatusEntry.name: eqlNASContainerStatusEntry
eqlNASContainerStatusEntry.description: An entry (row) containing NAS Container Status info.

eqlNASContainerStatusUsedSpace.name: eqlNASContainerStatusUsedSpace
eqlNASContainerStatusUsedSpace.description: Space used by NAS Containers including both snapshot space and filesystem usage)

eqlNASContainerStatusSnapshotSpace.name: eqlNASContainerStatusSnapshotSpace
eqlNASContainerStatusSnapshotSpace.description: Amount of used space in MB used by NAS Containers for storage of snapshot data. This is not snapshot reserve but rather snapshot reserve space currently in use. Initially this value would be 0.

eqlNASContainerStatusAllocatedSpace.name: eqlNASContainerStatusAllocatedSpace
eqlNASContainerStatusAllocatedSpace.description: Amount of space in MB allocated by NAS Containers

eqlNASContainerStatusFreeSpace.name: eqlNASContainerStatusFreeSpace
eqlNASContainerStatusFreeSpace.description: Amount of total free space in MB including both snapshot and filesystem

eqlNASContainerStatusOptimizationSpaceSa.name: eqlNASContainerStatusOptimizationSpaceSavings
eqlNASContainerStatusOptimizationSpaceSa.description: Amount of space saved in MB due to applying optimization

eqlNASContainerStatusOptimized.name: eqlNASContainerStatusOptimized
eqlNASContainerStatusOptimized.description: True if optimization was enabled once, false otherwise

eqlNASContainerStatusReplState.name: eqlNASContainerStatusReplState
eqlNASContainerStatusReplState.description: This column gives information about the replication status of this FileSystem. Standalone means the filesystem is not being replicated. Source means this filesystem is a source to a remote filesystem. Destination means this filesystem is destination for a source filesystem. Promoted means this filesystem used to be a destination but is right now promoted.

eqlNASContainerStatusNextSnapshotID.name: eqlNASContainerStatusNextSnapshotID
eqlNASContainerStatusNextSnapshotID.description: This column denotes the next SnapshotID avaiable for this particular container.

eqlNASApplianceNFSExportsTable.name: eqlNASApplianceNFSExportsTable
eqlNASApplianceNFSExportsTable.description: Equallogic-Dynamic NAS NFS Exports Table. This table contains a list of NFS exports configuration entry. TimeoutAll:60

eqlNASApplianceNFSExportsEntry.name: eqlNASApplianceNFSExportsEntry
eqlNASApplianceNFSExportsEntry.description: An entry (row) containing NFS exports configuration.

eqlNASApplianceNFSExportName.name: eqlNASApplianceNFSExportName
eqlNASApplianceNFSExportName.description: Contains only letters, digits and underscores. Must begin with a letter.

eqlNASApplianceNFSExportsRowStatus.name: eqlNASApplianceNFSExportsRowStatus
eqlNASApplianceNFSExportsRowStatus.description: Rowstatus variable used to manage this conceptual row.

eqlNASApplianceNFSExportDirectory.name: eqlNASApplianceNFSExportDirectory
eqlNASApplianceNFSExportDirectory.description: Full path to the Directory to be exported.

eqlNASApplianceNFSLimitReportedSize.name: eqlNASApplianceNFSLimitReportedSize
eqlNASApplianceNFSLimitReportedSize.description: Default value is zero and it means the actual size of NFS export will be returned. When the value is non-zeo, this value will be used instead of actual NFS Export size.

eqlNASApplianceNFSAccessClientIP.name: eqlNASApplianceNFSAccessClientIP
eqlNASApplianceNFSAccessClientIP.description: Value of this column along with eqlNASApplianceNFSAccessClientNetmask will determine access policy for clients

eqlNASApplianceNFSAccessClientNetmaskTyp.name: eqlNASApplianceNFSAccessClientNetmaskType
eqlNASApplianceNFSAccessClientNetmaskTyp.description: Type of eqlNASApplianceNFSAccessClientNetmask field. This value must match with eqlNASApplianceNFSAccessClientIPType field.

eqlNASApplianceNFSAccessClientNetmask.name: eqlNASApplianceNFSAccessClientNetmask
eqlNASApplianceNFSAccessClientNetmask.description: Value of this column along with eqlNASApplianceNFSAccessClientIP will determine access policy for clients

eqlNASApplianceNFSTrustUsers.name: eqlNASApplianceNFSTrustUsers
eqlNASApplianceNFSTrustUsers.description: Trusted users who can access the NFS Export

eqlNASApplianceNFSExportsFileId32bit.name: eqlNASApplianceNFSExportsFileId32bit
eqlNASApplianceNFSExportsFileId32bit.description: Determines 32-bit compatibility mode for this NFS export. When enabled, reported FileId (inode) information contains only lower 32-bits. When disabled, reported FileId (inode) information contains full 64-bit values.

eqlNASApplianceCIFSTable.name: eqlNASApplianceCIFSTable
eqlNASApplianceCIFSTable.description: Equallogic-Dynamic NAS CIFS Table. This table contains a list of CIFS configuration entry. TimeoutAll:60

eqlNASApplianceCIFSShareName.name: eqlNASApplianceCIFSShareName
eqlNASApplianceCIFSShareName.description: Contains only letters, digits and underscores.

eqlNASApplianceCIFSRowStatus.name: eqlNASApplianceCIFSRowStatus
eqlNASApplianceCIFSRowStatus.description: Rowstatus variable used to manage this conceptual row.

eqlNASApplianceCIFSExportedDirectory.name: eqlNASApplianceCIFSExportedDirectory
eqlNASApplianceCIFSExportedDirectory.description: Full Path to the directory to be exported.

eqlNASApplianceCIFSAllowGuestAccess.name: eqlNASApplianceCIFSAllowGuestAccess
eqlNASApplianceCIFSAllowGuestAccess.description: When set to true, guests will be allowed to access this share.

eqlNASApplianceCIFSLockEnforcement.name: eqlNASApplianceCIFSLockEnforcement
eqlNASApplianceCIFSLockEnforcement.description: Locking enforcement policy for this CIFS Share. This software release does not support changing the locking enforcement policy. Only the default option (all-locks) is supported.

eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusEnabled.name: eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusEnabled
eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusEnabled.description: When set to enabled, antivirus service will be enabled for this share. Else it will be disabled.

eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusPolicy.name: eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusPolicy
eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusPolicy.description: Determines the action to take when a file is found to be infected by a virus. This field is deprecated and unsupported. The value now always will be quarantine(0).

eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusExtensions.name: eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusExtensions
eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusExtensions.description: Comma-separated list of the file extensions which should / should not be virus-scanned. The value of the next field i.e. eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusExtensionsPolicy determines if the files with the corresponding extensions will be scanned or not for viruses. Cannot contain wild characters * and ?. Extensions are case-insensitive.

eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusExtensionsPo.name: eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusExtensionsPolicy
eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusExtensionsPo.description: Determines whether the files whose extensions match with those specified in the field above i.e. eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusExtensions, should be scanned OR should not be scanned for viruses. This field is deprecated and unsupported. The value now always will be exclude(0).

eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusExcludeDirPa.name: eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusExcludeDirPaths
eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusExcludeDirPa.description: Comma-separated list of the directory paths which should not be scanned for viruses. Paths can contain wildcards * and ?. NOTE: * will not match several path components.

eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusLargeFileSiz.name: eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusLargeFileSize
eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusLargeFileSiz.description: Determines the largest file size in MB which is sent to Antivirus server for scanning on the fly. The files larger than the specified size are not scanned. Access to these large files will be allowed or denied based on the CIFS Antivirus Large File Open policy.

eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusLargeFileOpe.name: eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusLargeFileOpen
eqlNASApplianceCIFSAntivirusLargeFileOpe.description: Determines if CIFS clients are allowed to open files larger than the value defined by CIFSAntivirusLargeFileSize.

eqlNASContainerDirectoryOpsTable.name: eqlNASContainerDirectoryOpsTable
eqlNASContainerDirectoryOpsTable.description: Equallogic-Dynamic NAS Container Directory Operations Table. This table is used for directory operations. TimeoutAll:60

eqlNASContainerDirectoryOpsIndex.name: eqlNASContainerDirectoryOpsIndex
eqlNASContainerDirectoryOpsIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifying a NAS container directory ops entry.

eqlNASContainerDirectoryRowStatus.name: eqlNASContainerDirectoryRowStatus
eqlNASContainerDirectoryRowStatus.description: Rowstatus variable used to manage directories. Operations supported will be create and delete. Get and Getnext operations on this table will return error.

eqlNASContainerDirectoryName.name: eqlNASContainerDirectoryName
eqlNASContainerDirectoryName.description: Full Path to the directory to be created or deleted. Ex: /home/user1. Create directory will fail if parent directory does not exist.

eqlNASContainerDirectoryCaseInsensitive.name: eqlNASContainerDirectoryCaseInsensitive
eqlNASContainerDirectoryCaseInsensitive.description: Determines whether the directory created is case insensitve or not.

eqlNASSnapshotTable.name: eqlNASSnapshotTable
eqlNASSnapshotTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic snapshot Table This table contains a list of snapshots associated with the associated container. TimeoutAll:60

eqlNASSnapshotEntry.name: eqlNASSnapshotEntry
eqlNASSnapshotEntry.description: An entry (row) containing snap shot info.

eqlNASSnapshotIndex.name: eqlNASSnapshotIndex
eqlNASSnapshotIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index which identifies a NAScontainer SnapShot.

eqlNASSnapshotName.name: eqlNASSnapshotName
eqlNASSnapshotName.description: This field specifies the friendly name used to identify a SnapShot. The name is auto-generated based on the NAScontainer name, optionally it can be provided or changed after the fact by the administrator.

eqlNASSnapshotSize.name: eqlNASSnapshotSize
eqlNASSnapshotSize.description: This field specifies the amount of space in MB a SnapShot consumes. Note: Deleting the SnapShot is not guaranteed to return the space specified, since a single block can be associated with multiple SnapShots. This value is xxxxc.

eqlNASSnapshotTimestamp.name: eqlNASSnapshotTimestamp
eqlNASSnapshotTimestamp.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY This field specifies the creation date/time for snapshot. Time is represented as the time in seconds since 00:00:00 UTC, 1970-01-01.

eqlNASSnapshotRollBack.name: eqlNASSnapshotRollBack
eqlNASSnapshotRollBack.description: True indicates the NASContainer is to be resotred to the state of this Snapshot.

eqlNASSnapshotPolicyIdx.name: eqlNASSnapshotPolicyIdx
eqlNASSnapshotPolicyIdx.description: This value identifies the snapshot policy for this snapshot.

eqlNASSnapshotPolicyTable.name: eqlNASSnapshotPolicyTable
eqlNASSnapshotPolicyTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent NAS SnapSnot Policy Table. TimeoutAll:60

eqlNASSnapshotPolicyEntry.name: eqlNASSnapshotPolicyEntry
eqlNASSnapshotPolicyEntry.description: An entry (row) containing NAS snapshot scheduling policy information.The policy determines when to create snapshot(s) of a appliance container.

eqlNASSnapshotPolicyIndex.name: eqlNASSnapshotPolicyIndex
eqlNASSnapshotPolicyIndex.description: This value uniquely identifies the snapshot policies for a container.

eqlNASSnapshotPolicyRowStatus.name: eqlNASSnapshotPolicyRowStatus
eqlNASSnapshotPolicyRowStatus.description: This value is used to manage the conceptual row.

eqlNASSnapshotPolicyName.name: eqlNASSnapshotPolicyName
eqlNASSnapshotPolicyName.description: This value specifies user friendly name for the policy. It is unique within the context of a volume. Spaces are not allowed.

eqlNASSnapshotPolicyMaxKeep.name: eqlNASSnapshotPolicyMaxKeep
eqlNASSnapshotPolicyMaxKeep.description: The value of this object determines the maximum no of snapshots created by this policy that can exist at a given time. When number of snapshots created by this policy reaches this value, for creating a new snapshot oldest snapshot created using this policy will be deleted. In a set operation, if the new value of this object is less than the old value, required number of oldest snapshots created by this policy will be deleted.

eqlNASSnapshotPolicyType.name: eqlNASSnapshotPolicyType
eqlNASSnapshotPolicyType.description: The value of this object determines the basic type of this policy. Except when set to once, the effective repetition period of the policy is determined using the value of this object along with the value of eqlNASSnapshotPolicyRepeatFactor. (See description of eqlNASSnapshotPolicyRepeatFactor for more information.)

eqlNASSnapshotPolicyRepeatFactor.name: eqlNASSnapshotPolicyRepeatFactor
eqlNASSnapshotPolicyRepeatFactor.description: The value of this object along with eqlNASSnapshotPolicyType determines the effective repetition interval for this policy. The valid values are PolicyType RepeatFactor once 1 hourly 1 daily 1-2147483647 weekly 1-2147483647 monthly 1-2147483647 If the policy type is daily and the value of this object is 2, snapshots will be taken once in every 2 days.

eqlNASSnapshotPolicyStartTime.name: eqlNASSnapshotPolicyStartTime
eqlNASSnapshotPolicyStartTime.description: The value of this object represents the time to start creating snapshot(s) within a day expressed as number of minutes from 12:00AM. The maximum value for this column is 24*60-1 which represents 11:59PM.

eqlNASSnapshotPolicyEndTime.name: eqlNASSnapshotPolicyEndTime
eqlNASSnapshotPolicyEndTime.description: The value of this object represents the time to stop creating snapshot(s) within a day expressed as number of minutes from 12:00AM. The maximum value for this column is 24*60-1 which represents 11:59PM. If eqlNASSnapshotPolicyType is once, the value of this column doesn't have any significance. If the value of this column is greater than start time, it represents end-time on the same day as start time. If the value is less than or equal to start time, it represents end-time on the next day of start time. This value doesnt have significance when frequency is set to zero. Endtime is exclusive when calculating no of snapshots. Example: StartTime EndTime Frequency NoofSnapshots 1320(10pm) 1380(11pm) 30mins 2 1320(10pm) 240(4am) 60mins 6 1320(10pm) 1320(10pm) 60mins 24 1320(10pm) 1319(9:59pm) 60mins 24 1320(10pm) - 0mins 1

eqlNASSnapshotPolicyTimeFrequency.name: eqlNASSnapshotPolicyTimeFrequency
eqlNASSnapshotPolicyTimeFrequency.description: The value of this object determines how frequent snapshots must be taken between start time and end time. This value doesn't have significance when policy type is set to once. For other policytypes, the value of end time is exclusive. For example if starttime is 180 (3:00AM) and endtime is 240(4:00AM), when frequency is set to 30, snapshots will be created at 3:00AM, 3:30AM. If the value is zero, it represents invalid frequency and in such case, end time doesnt have significance.

eqlNASSnapshotPolicyStartDate.name: eqlNASSnapshotPolicyStartDate
eqlNASSnapshotPolicyStartDate.description: The value of this object determines the date from which the policy will be active. By default, this is the policy creation date. The value is expressed as number of days since epoch.

eqlNASSnapshotPolicyEndDate.name: eqlNASSnapshotPolicyEndDate
eqlNASSnapshotPolicyEndDate.description: The value of this object determines the date after which the policy will be inactive.It doesnt have significance when policy type is once. Default value is the mamixum value allowed. When set to maximum value, the policy will be active until it gets deleted. The value is expressed as number of days since epoch.

eqlNASSnapshotPolicyWeekMask.name: eqlNASSnapshotPolicyWeekMask
eqlNASSnapshotPolicyWeekMask.description: The value of this column is significant only if policytype is set to weekly or monthly. When the value is 0x7fffffff, it represents a special meaning to the value of occurence. See the description for occurence below. The LSB to LSB+6 bits of the mask are significant. Each bit represents a day in the week with LSB being Mon and LSB+6 being Sun. If mask is 0x00000041 - snapshots will be created on Monday and Sunday. If mask is 0x0000007f - snapshots will be created on all weekdays which is effectively a daily policy. If mask is 0x0000001f, it represents week days.If mask is 0x00000060, it represents weekend days.

eqlNASSnapshotPolicyMonthMask.name: eqlNASSnapshotPolicyMonthMask
eqlNASSnapshotPolicyMonthMask.description: The value of this column is currently not being used.

eqlNASSnapshotPolicyOccurence.name: eqlNASSnapshotPolicyOccurence
eqlNASSnapshotPolicyOccurence.description: The value of this column is significant only if the policy type is set to monthly. If weekmask is set to 0x7fffffff, the value of this column represents the occurence of a day with in a month. Example:If the value of this column is 5, it represents 5th day of the month. When the week mask is set to a value other than 0x7fffffff, the value of this column defines the occurence of a day as defined by weekmask. Example: When weekmask is set to 0x00000001 (Monday) and value of this column represents the following. Value Meaning 0x1 First monday of the month 0x2 Second monday of the month 0x3 Third monday of the month 0x4 Fourth monday of the month 0x7fffffff Last monday of the month
